  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "During the last fuzzing call, it was agreed that extra `debug_*` APIs should be implemented. Specifically, the APIs are:\n* `debug_getBadBlocks`\n* `debug_standardTraceBlockToFile`\n* `debug_standardTraceBadBlockToFile`\n\nA specification can be found here: https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/rpc/ns-debug#debug_standardtraceblocktofile\n\nMore context: \n\n> `debug_getBadBlocks` helps identify the block, but geth also has `debug_standardTraceBlockToFile` to dump out all traces to disk (it’s usually not possible to dump out 12M-gas blocks over RPC). However, that’s only half, we also have `debug_standardTraceBadBlockToFile` to execute a ‘bad’ block and get the trace there too. \n> If Open Ethereum also supported those two methods, the time required to identify a random opcode mismatch would be very small\n",
